Write a function called filterPrimeNumbers that filters prime numbers from an array. A prime number is only divisible by 1 and itself.


Examples:

// Example 1
Input: [4, 7, 12, 11, 15, 17, 20, 23]
Output: [7, 11, 17, 23]

// Example 2
Input: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]
Output: [2, 3, 5]  // Note: 1 is not prime

// Example 3
Input: [91, 92, 93, 97, 98, 99]
Output: [97]